    {
      "id": 128,
      "title": "v3.3 [TIER-A] Fix session reset logic: change from rolling 5h window to fixed-interval hard reset in server/routes/usage.ts",
      "description": "server/routes/usage.ts implements session as a rolling 5-hour window via startSession() (start time + 5h). Actual Claude behavior is a HARD reset every 5 hours on a fixed schedule — not relative to first usage. The rolling window causes the estimator to show wrong countdown values after breaks. Fix: accept reset_in_minutes from the user as the authoritative source of when the current window expires, don't recalculate from startSession.",
