    {
      "id": 129,
      "title": "v3.5 [P0] Route-level API tests — generate Vitest tests for all 35 routes via supertest or direct fetch",
      "description": "The single biggest risk in the codebase. 7,500 lines of server code with zero HTTP-level tests. Store tests pass but route logic (validation, error codes, auth, serialization) is completely unverified. Generate tests by reading each route file and producing assertion patterns. Should cover: status codes, body shapes, error responses, edge cases. Target: at least 1 test per route endpoint. Use the existing test infrastructure (Vitest, in-process store) but add HTTP-level assertions.",
