    },
    {
      "id": 131,
      "title": "v3.5 [P1] nexus.json backup rotation + corruption detection on startup",
      "description": "Single point of failure: all metabrain data in one JSON file. On every _flush, rotate: nexus.json → nexus.json.bak. On startup, validate JSON parse succeeds — if not, fall back to .bak. Optionally: keep last 3 backups (nexus.json.bak.1, .2, .3). Simple, zero-dependency, protects 88 decisions + 52 sessions + 500 activity entries from corruption.",
      "status": "done",
      "priority": 2,
      "sort_order": 40,
      "linked_files": "[]",
      "created_at": "2026-04-09T19:55:36.564Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-09T20:47:40.322Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 132,
      "title": "v3.5 [P1] Auto-link decisions on record — when nexus_record_decision fires, search Ledger for related decisions and propose typed edges",
      "description": "Makes the Knowledge Graph self-organizing. When a new decision is recorded (via MCP or CLI), automatically: (1) search existing decisions for keyword overlap, (2) if similarity > threshold, create a 'related' edge. Optional: use local AI to determine edge type (led_to / depends_on / contradicts). This closes the gap where decisions are recorded but never connected — the most common Knowledge Graph quality issue.",
      "status": "backlog",
      "priority": 1,
      "sort_order": 41,
