    {
      "id": 133,
      "title": "v3.5 [P1] SessionStart hook: fix project detection — use git remote origin, package.json name, or nearest .claude config instead of CWD basename",
      "description": "Current hook uses process.cwd().split('/').pop() which gives 'Projects' when launched from C:\\Projects. Better detection order: (1) check for .nexus-project file in CWD, (2) read package.json name, (3) parse git remote origin URL, (4) fall back to CWD basename. Small fix, big UX impact — every session starts with wrong project context otherwise.",
      "status": "backlog",
      "priority": 1,
