      "title": "v3.5 [P2] Fuel estimator: return LAST REPORTED value as primary, extrapolated as secondary — implement the static-fuel feedback rule server-side",
      "description": "Currently /api/estimator extrapolates burn rate over time, showing fuel ticking down during breaks. The user explicitly asked for STATIC values (feedback_fuel_display.md). Fix: the estimator response should have { reported: { session, weekly, timestamp }, estimated: { session, weekly }, source: 'reported' | 'estimated' }. Brief and hooks show reported values. Estimated is secondary/labeled.",
