      "id": 77,
      "decision": "Noosphere uses Hebbian learning instead of backpropagation for agent neural networks",
      "context": "Biologically plausible (brains don't do backprop), runs entirely in GLSL compute shaders without needing PyTorch/libtorch, produces weirder and more emergent behavior than gradient-trained nets, no backward pass means massive parallelism",
      "project": "general",
      "alternatives": [
        "Option A: PyTorch via libtorch GDExtension — rejected for build complexity and less interesting dynamics. Option B: Evolutionary strategies — considered as alternative",
        "keeps as fallback. Option C: Neuroevolution (NEAT) — too slow for real-time learning."
      ],
      "tags": [],
      "created_at": "2026-04-07T16:17:49.869Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 78,
      "decision": "Noosphere uses Godot 4.6.1 compute shaders via RenderingDevice API instead of raw CUDA",
      "context": "Cross-platform Vulkan, built-in renderer, UI, audio, scene tree, and input handling — we only need to write the GLSL. 8GB VRAM on RTX 3070 Ti is far more than the ~14MB compute budget, so rendering and compute coexist cleanly. Hot-reload potential for shaders. No external build pipeline.",
      "project": "general",
      "alternatives": [
        "Option A: Raw CUDA + custom renderer — rejected",
        "months of infrastructure work. Option B: Python + CuPy + pygame — rejected",
        "too slow for real-time rendering of field. Option C: Unity with compute shaders — possible but Godot 4.6.1 already on machine and lighter weight."
      ],
      "tags": [],
      "created_at": "2026-04-07T16:17:55.845Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 79,
      "decision": "Noosphere tensor field: 64x64x32 grid with 16 channels, PDE solver via wave equation + diffusion + damping",
      "context": "Field is the communication substrate and the game's narrator. Channel layout: 0-3 semantic, 4-5 emotion, 6-7 causal, 8-9 resources, 10-11 social, 12-13 player, 14-15 memory. 8MB VRAM double-buffered for Verlet integration. Workgroup (8,8,8) dispatched over full volume.",
      "project": "general",
      "alternatives": [
        "Option A: Smaller 32^3 field — insufficient spatial detail. Option B: Larger 128^3 — 8x memory",
        "not needed for target 60 agents. Option C: 2D field — rejected",
        "loses volumetric dynamics that make emergent standing waves interesting."
      ],
      "tags": [],
      "created_at": "2026-04-07T16:18:02.168Z"
    },
    {
