      "decision": "v3.3 patch scope: Nexus-augmented audit found ~25 issues across server, client, docs/CLI. Tier A (must-ship): version sync drift (welcome v2.0, mcp help v3.1, package versions), CLI/MCPB tool list staleness (lists 6, actual 18), WebSocket infinite-reconnect bug, deleteScratchpad missing _flush, sessions.ts unsafe Object.assign, Compass minutesAgo NaN guards. Tier B: modal a11y (role/aria-modal/focus trap), form validation (Missions/Bookmarks/Overseer), mobile breakpoints (Pulse/ProjectHealth grids), POST input validation, parseInt clamping. Tier C: 36 (store as any) casts → typed accessors, ErrorBoundary async limitation, nexus_brief MCP project filter improvement, stale Ledger entries cleanup. Audit performed via parallel Explore agents + native MCP recon (brief, critique, predict, search) — first audit conducted entirely through the v3.2 toolset, demonstrating the metabrain auditing itself.</decision>\n<parameter name=\"rationale\">Audit caught real bugs (deleteScratchpad persistence, WebSocket reconnect storm, NaN in Compass) plus systemic tech debt (36 type holes). Prioritization is fuel-aware: Tier A is ~2 hours of focused work, Tier B is ~3 hours, Tier C is multi-session. Recommend Tier A as v3.3, Tier B as v3.4, Tier C as ongoing.",
      "context": "",
      "project": "Nexus",
      "alternatives": [],
      "tags": [],
      "created_at": "2026-04-07T19:47:43.349Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 88,
      "decision": "v3.4 shipped Claude Code hooks for passive metabrain growth. SessionStart hook injects context automatically, Stop hook auto-generates AI session summary. This closes the last gap in the metabrain loop: sessions are now recorded passively without manual nexus_log_session calls. The metabrain grows even when the user forgets.",
      "context": "Two hooks chosen for v3.4 because they have the highest leverage with lowest risk. PostToolUse (file activity logging) deferred due to noise concerns; UserPromptSubmit (guard check) deferred due to latency concerns. Both are natural v3.5 candidates once debouncing infrastructure exists.",
      "project": "Nexus",
      "alternatives": [],
      "tags": [],
      "created_at": "2026-04-09T19:45:23.984Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 89,
      "decision": "v3.5 roadmap: 6 tasks ranked by leverage. P0: route-level API tests (biggest risk — 7,500 lines untested) + async ask_overseer (unblocks 200k context vision). P1: nexus.json backup rotation (single point of failure), auto-link decisions on record (self-organizing Knowledge Graph), SessionStart project detection fix (CWD-based is broken). P2: fuel estimator static values (implement feedback rule server-side). The recursive insight: each version's tools make the next version faster to build. v3.5 should be the version where the metabrain starts improving itself — auto-linking, self-testing, self-healing data.",
      "context": "Reflection on full conversation arc from v3.0 to v3.4. 17K lines of code, 49 commits, 88 decisions, 52 sessions, 18 MCP tools, 2 lifecycle hooks. The biggest gap is test coverage (zero route-level tests) which the Overseer also flagged. The biggest opportunity is the recursive improvement loop — tools that make themselves better.",
